{"componentChunkName":"component---src-layouts-blog-post-layout-js","path":"/blog/how-to-fix-broken-zoom-on-shopify-refresh-theme","result":{"pageContext":{"id":2206,"date":"2023-01-29T16:44:36","date_gmt":"2023-01-29T16:44:36","guid":{"rendered":"https://www.ezfy.club/?p=2206"},"modified":"2023-03-09T17:12:55","modified_gmt":"2023-03-09T17:12:55","slug":"how-to-fix-broken-zoom-on-shopify-refresh-theme","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https://www.ezfy.club/how-to-fix-broken-zoom-on-shopify-refresh-theme/","title":{"rendered":"How to fix broken zoom on “Refresh” theme"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>The Refresh theme combines a color pallet that is strong but easy on the eyes with a clean, modern looking interface to leave a strong impression on potential buyers as soon as they open your website.<br><br>While that is a strong draw towards your products, the default zoom functionality for the product page provided by Shopify leaves much to be desired: poor navigation and zoom optimization that affect not only desktop users, but are particularly harsh on mobile visitors. Together, these issues provide a poor browsing experience for potential buyers that can seriously hurt their first impression of your brand.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Using this easy to install copy and paste code snippet you can strengthen your Refresh theme store by allowing your clients to view product images with varying levels of zoom that are easy to interact with even at the highest level, providing an optimal experience both on desktop and mobile devices that&#8217;s worth of your store!<br><br>Take a look at how it works in practice in our <a href=\"https://refresh-password-is-123.myshopify.com/products/ezfy-zoom\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">live preview</a>. (Password: <strong>123</strong>)</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Making a backup of your theme</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Before diving into the tutorial make sure you download the theme, so in case you face any issues you can easily revert back.<br><br><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1514\" height=\"481\" class=\"wp-image-503\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/dl-123.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/dl-123.png 1514w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/dl-123-600x191.png 600w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/dl-123-1200x381.png 1200w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/dl-123-768x244.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1514px) 100vw, 1514px\" /></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"h-downloading-the-code-files\">Downloading the code files</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>You can download the code files <a href=\"https://ezfycode.com/shop/refresh-theme-zoom-slider-pro\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">clicking here</a>. (<a href=\"https://refresh-password-is-123.myshopify.com/products/ezfy-zoom\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">live preview</a>)</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"h-getting-the-code\">Getting the code</h3>\n\n\n\n<ol>\n<li>Starting from your Shopify admin, navigate through&nbsp;<strong>Online Store</strong>&nbsp;&gt;&nbsp;<strong>Themes&nbsp;</strong>&gt;&nbsp;<strong>Actions&nbsp;</strong>&gt;&nbsp;<strong>Edit Code</strong>.<br><br><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1254\" height=\"367\" class=\"wp-image-2238\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/refresh-edit-code.png\" alt=\"Opening the code editor in the refresh theme\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/refresh-edit-code.png 1254w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/refresh-edit-code-850x249.png 850w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/refresh-edit-code-1200x351.png 1200w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/refresh-edit-code-768x225.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1254px) 100vw, 1254px\" /><br></li>\n\n\n\n<li>Check the <a href=\"https://ezfycode.com/shop/refresh-theme-zoom-slider-pro\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">.zip you downloaded</a>, inside you&#8217;ll find the following file:<br> <br><strong>ezfy-zoom.txt</strong><br><br>Open it and copy all the code inside it.</li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"h-creating-the-file-for-the-code\">Creating the file for the code</h3>\n\n\n\n<ol>\n<li>Go back to the Shopify code editor you just opened and look for the <strong>Snippets</strong> folder. Click on &#8220;<em>Add a new snippet</em>&#8221; and name it exactly: <br><br><strong>ezfy-zoom</strong><br><br><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1401\" height=\"698\" class=\"wp-image-894\" style=\"width: 650px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/ezfy-zoom1.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/ezfy-zoom1.png 1401w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/ezfy-zoom1-600x299.png 600w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/ezfy-zoom1-1200x598.png 1200w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/ezfy-zoom1-768x383.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1401px) 100vw, 1401px\" /><br></li>\n\n\n\n<li>Paste the code that you copied from the <strong>ezfy-zoom.txt</strong> file and click on <strong>save</strong>.<br><br><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1564\" height=\"438\" class=\"wp-image-896\" style=\"width: 600px;\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/ezfy-zoom-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/ezfy-zoom-2.jpg 1564w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/ezfy-zoom-2-600x168.jpg 600w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/ezfy-zoom-2-1200x336.jpg 1200w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/ezfy-zoom-2-768x215.jpg 768w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/ezfy-zoom-2-1536x430.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1564px) 100vw, 1564px\" /></li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<h3>Connecting the code to your theme</h3>\n\n\n\n<ol>\n<li>Find the file named <strong>theme.liquid</strong> by using the search bar or looking in the <strong>Layout</strong> folder.<br></li>\n\n\n\n<li>Once inside it press CTRL + F (or CMD + F on Mac) to open the search bar and look for:<br><br><strong>&lt;/body&gt;</strong><br></li>\n\n\n\n<li>Directly&nbsp;<strong>above&nbsp;</strong>the&nbsp;<strong>&lt;/body&gt;</strong>&nbsp;tag you found paste the following code and then click on save:<br><br><code>{% include 'ezfy-zoom' %}</code><br></li>\n</ol>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"720\" height=\"698\" src=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/ezfy-zoom-3.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-898\" srcset=\"https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/ezfy-zoom-3.jpg 720w, https://www.ezfy.club/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/ezfy-zoom-3-600x582.jpg 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Conclusion</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>This is all you needed to do! You can now click on the magnifying glass icon found in any of your product page images and you&#8217;ll see a much improved zoom effect. <br><br>And if anything didn&#8217;t work as intended, contact us at <strong>ezfycode@gmail.com</strong> and we&#8217;ll get back to you as soon as possible ready to assist.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://ezfycode.com/blog/add-slideshow-shopify-no-apps\">&#8211; How to make slideshow images stop cutting off</a><iframe loading=\"lazy\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/UKO9ViFXaWQ\" title=\"YouTube video player\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" allowfullscreen=\"\"><br><a href=\"https://ezfycode.com/blog/collection-with-tabs-shopify-section-tutorial\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">&#8211; Add a collection tabs slider to any store (copy/paste, no apps, blazing fast)</a><iframe loading=\"lazy\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/